owl:Ontology.terms:description: This ontology describes the OpenStreetMap data model.
owl:Ontology.rdfs:label: OpenStreetMaps Vocabulary

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Used to describe the legal access for highways and other transportation networks.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: access=*

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A barrier is a physical structure which blocks or impedes movement.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: barrier=*

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Used to describe a feature which is currently under construction.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: construction=*

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: This tag is used for more accurately describing specific types of pedestrian crossings.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: crossing=*

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Maps cycling infrastructure that is an inherent part of the road.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: cycleway=*

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: An ordered collection of nodes that describe the way. These may be fragmented over multiple predicates due to tiling for example. Each fragment should have enough overlap to reconstruct the original way.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: hasNodes

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: This the main property used to identify any kind of road, street or path.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: highway=*

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Legal access restriction for all motor vehicles.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: motor_vehicle=*

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Indicate the access restriction on highways and other linear features.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: oneway=*

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Defines the oneway rules for cyclists.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: oneway:bicycle=*

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Used for combined cycle- and footways.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: segregated=*

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Provides a classification scheme regarding the physical usability of a way.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: smoothness=*

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Provides information about the physical surface of elements, particularly regarding material composition and/or structure.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: surface=*

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Measures how well-maintained a track is, particularly regarding surface firmness.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: tracktype=*

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Legal access restriction for all types of land-based vehicles not operated upon rails.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: vehicle=*

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: A tag describes the meaning of a particular element in the OSM data model. It consists of two free format text fields; a 'key' and a 'value' and are formatted as '{key}={value}'. This property should be used for tags that don't have their semantics explicitly defined.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: hasTag

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Used to define the maximum legal speed limit, in km/h.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: maxspeed=*

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Used to describe the legal access for highways and other transportation networks.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: AccessValue

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A barrier is a physical structure which blocks or impedes movement.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: BarrierValue

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Used to describe a feature which is currently under construction.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: ConstructionValue

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: This tag is used for more accurately describing specific types of pedestrian crossings.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: CrossingValue

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Maps cycling infrastructure that is an inherent part of the road.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: CyclewayValue

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Elements are the basic components of OpenStreetMap's conceptual data model of the physical world.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Element

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Indicates the role and importance of the way within the road network.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: HighwayValue

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A node is one of the core elements in the OpenStreetMap data model. It consists of a single point in space defined by its latitude, longitude and node id.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Node

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Indicate the access restriction on highways and other linear features.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: OnewayValue

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A relation consists of one or more tags and also an ordered list of one or more nodes, ways and/or relations as members. It is used to define logical or geographic relationships between other elements.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Relation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Provides a classification scheme regarding the physical usability of a way.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: SmoothnessValue

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Provides information about the physical surface of elements, particularly regarding material composition and/or structure.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: SurfaceValue

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Measures how well-maintained a track is, particularly regarding surface firmness.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: TracktypeValue

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A way is an ordered list of nodes which normally also has at least one tag.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Way

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Only for agricultural traffic.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: access=agricultural

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: This road has an asphalt surface.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: surface=asphalt

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Usable by trekking bikes, normal cars and everything that can use roads with 'very bad' smoothness.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: smoothness=bad

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: This is not a oneway street.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: oneway=no

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A large, solid, immobile block that can be moved only with heavy machinery or great effort.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: barrier=block

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Solid (usually concrete or metal) pillar or pillars in the middle of the road to prevent passage by some traffic.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: barrier=bollard

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: This is a control point at an international border between two countries. Passports or other forms of ID will be checked.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: barrier=border_control

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A way intended for use by horse riders.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: highway=bridleway

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A bump gate is a drive-through gate used in rural areas to provide a barrier to livestock that does not require the driver to exit the vehicle.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: barrier=bump_gate

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A bus trap is a metal grate placed over a ditch or pit in the road with tines (sides) spaced far enough apart that small-diameter-wheeled (narrower axle) vehicles fall in between the tines but close enough that larger-diameter-wheeled vehicles, such as buses, may pass.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: barrier=bus_trap

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Bars in the road surface that allow wheeled vehicles but not animals to cross.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: barrier=cattle_grid

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A chain used to prevent motorised vehicles.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: barrier=chain

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: This road has an cobblestone surface.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: surface=cobblestone

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A mixture of larger (e.g., gravel) and smaller (e.g., sand) parts, compacted so the surface is more stable than loose gravel.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: surface=compacted

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Cement based concrete.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: surface=concrete

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Only for customers of the element.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: access=customers

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Barriers to bicycle traffic, most typically a pair of staggered steel bars perpendicular to the way itself whose gaps allow pedestrians to pass.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: barrier=cycle_barrier

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: For designated cycleways.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: highway=cycleway

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A road is blocked by debris with or without ground. This might be for short or long time. Often used as first step in blocking an abandoned road.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: barrier=debris

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Only when delivering to the element.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: access=customers

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A preferred or designated route.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: access=designated

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Only when travelling to this element/area; i.e., local traffic only.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: access=destination

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: This road's surface is just dirt (earth).
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: surface=dirt

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A legal right of way exists but usage is officially discouraged.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: access=discouraged

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Permitted for some vehicle (or animal) only if you dismount.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: access=dismount

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Only for emergency vehicles.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: access=emergency

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A gap in a linear barrier with nothing that limits passing through.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: barrier=entrance

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Usable by roller blades, skate boards and everything that can use roads with 'good' smoothness.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: smoothness=excellent

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A multilayer pavement with a stone or gravel basis and a topmost surface of firm, granular gravel.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: surface=fine_gravel

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Designated footpaths; i.e., mainly/exclusively for pedestrians.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: highway=footway

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Only for forestry traffic.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: access=forestry

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The public has an official, legally-enshrined right of access; i.e., it's a right of way.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: access=yes

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: An entrance that can be opened or closed to get through the barrier.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: barrier=gate

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Points where a traffic sign instructs traffic to cede priority.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: highway=give_way

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Usable by racing bikes and everything that can use roads with 'intermediate' smoothness.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: smoothness=good

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Solid. Usually a paved or sealed surface.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: tracktype=grade1

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Solid. Usually an unpaved track with surface of gravel.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: tracktype=grade2

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Mostly solid. Even mixture of hard and soft materials.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: tracktype=grade3

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Mostly soft. Almost always an unpaved track prominently with soil/sand/grass, but with some hard or compacted materials mixed in.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: tracktype=grade4

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Soft. Almost always an unpaved track lacking additional materials, same surface as surrounding terrain.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: tracktype=grade5

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Grass covered ground.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: surface=grass

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Broken/crushed rock with sharp edges.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: surface=gravel

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: No special surface, the ground itself has marks of human or animal usage.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: surface=ground

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Pedestrians can cross a street here.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: highway=crossing

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Usable by heavy-duty off-road vehicles and everything that can use roads with 'very horrible' smoothness.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: smoothness=horrible

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Not usable by wheeled vehicles.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: smoothness=impassable

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: This is a oneway street, with the direction being the same order of the way nodes.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: oneway=yes

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: This is a oneway street, with the direction being the reverse of the order of the way nodes.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: oneway=-1

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Usable by city bikes, sport cars, wheel chairs and everything that can use roads with 'bad' smoothness.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: smoothness=intermediate

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Two-way streets where there are cycle lanes on both sides of the road.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: cycleway=lane

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A lift gate (boom barrier) is a bar, or pole pivoted in such a way as to allow the boom to block vehicular access through a controlled point.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: barrier=lift_gate

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: For living streets, which are residential streets where pedestrians have legal priority over cars.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: highway=living_street

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A restricted access major divided highway, normally with 2 or more running lanes plus emergency hard shoulder.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: highway=motorway

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The link roads leading to/from a motorway.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: highway=motorway_link

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Like the ground surface, but usually wet.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: surface=mud

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: No access for the general public.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: access=no

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A way legally dedicated to specific modes of travel by a law or by the rules of traffic.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: access=official

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Cyclists are permitted to travel in both directions on a road which is one-way for normal traffic.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: cycleway=opposite

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A one-way street that has a cycling lane going in the opposite direction to normal traffic flow.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: cycleway=opposite_lane

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A cycle track travelling in the opposite direction to other traffic.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: cycleway=opposite_track

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A non-specific path.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: highway=path

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A non-specific paved surface.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: surface=paved

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A relatively smooth surface paved with stones.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: surface=paving_stones

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Loosely arranged smooth stones.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: surface=pebblestone

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Open to general traffic until such time as the owner revokes the permission.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: access=permissive

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The next most important roads in a country's system, after trunks.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: highway=primary

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The link roads leading to/from a primary road.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: highway=primary_link

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Only with individual permission.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: access=private

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: For roads that are about to be built, but where any construction work hasn't yet been started.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: highway=proposed

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Roads which serve as an access to housing, without function of connecting settlements. Often lined with housing.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: highway=residential

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: This tag is used for a road with an unknown classification.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: highway=road

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A sally port is used to pass through thick or city walls, and is a type of covered gate with two doors.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: barrier=sally_port

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Small to very small fractions of rock.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: surface=sand

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The next most important roads in a country's system, after primary roads.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: highway=secondary

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The link roads leading to/from a secondary road.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: highway=secondary_link

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: For access roads to, or within an industrial estate, camp site, business park, car park etc.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: highway=service

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Sett paving, formed from natural stones cut to a regular shape. The stones do not cover the surface completely, unlike paving_stones.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: surface=sett

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A cycle lane taking the form of a bus lane that is also designated for use by cyclists.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: cycleway=share_busway

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: In general, this indicates that cyclists share space with other traffic on this highway.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: cycleway=shared

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Roads which contain a shared lane marking, or sharrow, to indicate that the travel lane is shared by bicycles and other vehicles.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: cycleway=shared_lane

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A sidewalk that's distinct from the carriageway.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: footway=sidewalk

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Flights of steps on footways and paths.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: highway=steps

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Points at which vehicles are required to stop.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: highway=stop

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Similar to a lift gate but rotates sidewards to open.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: barrier=swing_gate

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The next most important roads in a country's system, after secondary roads.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: highway=tertiary

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The link roads leading to/from a tertiary road.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: highway=tertiary_link

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A road usage toll or fee is collected here.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: barrier=toll_booth

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Roads for mostly agricultural or forestry uses. If used in the context of a cycleway this means a cycle track running parallel to a road.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: highway=track

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Signalling devices positioned at road intersections, pedestrian crossings and other locations to control competing flows of traffic.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: highway=traffic_signals

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The most important roads in a country's system that aren't motorways.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: highway=trunk

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The link roads leading to/from a trunk road.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: highway=trunk_link

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A turnstile (also called baffle gate) is used to allow one person at a time to pass.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: barrier=turnstile

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The least important through roads in a country's system.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: highway=unclassified

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A generic crossing with no traffic-signals of any type, just road markings.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: crossing=uncontrolled

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Indicates that this element is under construction.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: construction=yes

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Cobblestone paving, formed from natural, uncut, overall rounded stones. Firmly attached to a ground, unlike pebblestone.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: surface=unhewn_cobblestone

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A crossing without road markings or traffic lights
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: crossing=unmarked

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A loose covering ranging from compacted stone chippings to earth.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: surface=unpaved

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Can only be used in countries with compulsory cycleways and gives access information on parallel roads.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: access=use_sidepath

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Usable by cars with high clearance, light-duty off-road vehicles and everything that can use roads with 'horrible' smoothness.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: smoothness=very_bad

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Usable by tractors, ATVs and tanks.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: smoothness=very_horrible

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Wood.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: surface=wood
